
  Name:  clock
  
  #include <time.h>
  clock_t clock(void);
  
  The clock( ) function returns a value that approximates the 
  amount of time the calling program has been running. To transform
  this value into seconds, divide it by CLOCKS_PER_SEC.
                                              
  Example:
  void elapsed_time(void)
  {
    printf(''Elapsed time: %u secs.\n", clock()/CLOCKS_PER_SEC);
  }

  Related Functions:  time, asctime, and ctime

